content: The 3,150 m long Lefortovo tunnel in Russia, (near Poland ) is the longest in-city tunnel in all of Europe. It is nicknamed "The Tunnel of Death." See for yourself why. There is a river running over the tunnel and water leaks through in some areas. When the temperature reaches nearly 0 º C like it does during the winter in Russia, the road freezes and becomes a sheet of black ice. The result is the attached video which was taken during a single day with the tunnel surveillance cameras. Must do wonders for the cost of their auto insurance! Congratulations to the dual-carriage bus driver -- imagine the passengers in the back! What a ride! The next time you complain about traffic, remember this video... Yikes, Russian engineering... or... Perhaps it's the ... vodka. "http://s10.photobucket.com/albums/a123/Samualclemmons/?action=view&current=Russian_Tunnel_of_Death.flv" How come I pressed "One for English" and still can't understand a word the dude is saying?
